<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7363> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7363" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In the SC de Sarapeo Deli Insulae (SIG(3) 664; Sherk, RDGE no. 5, 37-39, ca. 164) the tribe is not given with the names of the other two witnesses. L. R. Taylor (VDRR 204) suggests that it is given in order to distinguish him from other branches of the Claudii such as the Nerones, who were in Arnensis. His cognomen could have been Asellus.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6848> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6848" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator soon after 166 (SIG(3) 664-I. de Delos 4.1.1510)." .
